alactic nuclei SEDs, our targets have a brighter dust torus and redder optical{\textendash}IR colour. By comparing the SED to JWST 'little red dots' (LRDs), we find that these IR-selected type 2 QSOs have similar SED shapes to the LRDs. This survey demonstrates mid-IR selection as an efficient method to find luminous type 2 QSOs and the composite photometry generated by this sample provides a guide for finding more type 2 QSOs at higher redshift in the future.}},
